    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Campanula biebersteiniana are gastrointestinal issues, such as diarrhea and stomach cramps, which are often caused by its anthelmintic and antiparasitic properties that help eliminate worms and parasites from the digestive system. Its anti-inflammatory properties also alleviate respiratory problems, including bronchitis and asthma, by reducing inflammation and congestion in the airways. Additionally, Campanula biebersteiniana is used to treat dermatological conditions, like eczema and acne, due to its antiseptic and antibacterial properties that help combat infections and reduce inflammation. Furthermore, its diuretic properties make it an effective remedy for kidney stones and urinary tract infections by increasing urine production and flushing out toxins from the body. Its antispasmodic properties also relieve menstrual cramps and spasms by relaxing the uterine muscles and reducing pain.",
