    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Campanula biebersteiniana are its anti-inflammatory effects, which have been attributed to the presence of flavonoids and saponins. This plant also exhibits antioxidant properties, reducing oxidative stress and protecting cells from damage, a function that can be linked to the action of volatile oils. Additionally, Campanula biebersteiniana has been found to possess antimicrobial activity, inhibiting the growth of various pathogens, a property that can be attributed to its content of glycosides and phenolic acids. Furthermore, the plant has been reported to display wound-healing properties, accelerating tissue repair and regeneration, a function that may be related to the presence of ascorbic acid and other biologically active compounds. Its antiseptic and antiviral properties, on the other hand, have been linked to the action of iridoids and other bioactive molecules.",
