    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Campanula biebersteiniana are tincture, infusion, tea, salve, and decoction. Campanula biebersteiniana tincture is a concentrated liquid solution obtained through the extraction of the plant's aerial parts using a solvent, typically ethanol, and is used to treat respiratory issues and as an antispasmodic. Infusion is a liquid solution prepared by steeping the aerial parts of Campanula biebersteiniana in hot water to create a tea that is used to treat digestive issues and as an expectorant. Tea, also known as an infusion, is prepared similarly but in a more diluted form and is used to treat respiratory issues and as an antispasmodic. Campanula biebersteiniana salve is a topical preparation made from the plant's aerial parts and is used to treat skin issues such as wounds and inflammation, while decoction is a concentrated liquid solution prepared by boiling the plant's roots in water to create a liquid used to treat digestive issues.",
